Student and Company commands: change duplicate criteria
commitResults.messageBody:
Student duplicates are now handled by Student ID instead of Name, and
Company duplicates are now determined by both Industry and Name. This
enhances data integrity by ensuring unique identification for students
and companies.

Let's improve the uniqueness handling to better support contact
management requirements.

commitResults.messageTitle: Student command: change Student ID prefix from s/ to id/
commitResults.messageBody:
Changing the Student ID prefix from s/ to id/ to prevent conflicts when
names contain slashes, such as "John s/o Doe". This update allows names
with slashes to be added without triggering errors due to delimiter
confusion.

Fixes #124.

commitResults.messageTitle: Refactor ExportCommandTest for cross-platform path compatibility  - Updated relative and absolute file path handling in ExportCommandTest to use platform-independent Paths.get() for consistent results across Unix and Windows environments. - Added cleanup steps to ensure temporary files and directories are deleted after tests, preventing conflicts in CI. - Enhanced file reading with Files.newBufferedReader for simplified handling of file encoding and paths.
Update export CSV handling for windows compatibility

Refactor ImportCommand path validation and update error handling  - Added validateFilePath method for modular validation of file paths in ImportCommand. - Refined execute to catch IllegalArgumentException and rethrow as CommandException for UI compatibility. - Enhanced test cases for execute validation, addressing both absolute and relative paths. - Improved error messages to guide users on correct path formats, including .csv extension and character restrictions.

Enhance ImportCommand path validation for Windows compatibility  - Refine ImportCommand constructor to handle Windows-specific path issues. - Reject paths starting with `/` or `\` without a drive letter on Windows. - Update invalid path test cases to account for Windows and Unix-like differences. - Ensure error messages clearly communicate correct file path format.
